main event: A civilian reported observing a UFO in Atkins, Arkansas for approximately 20-25 minutes on January 26, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as having varied courses and was reported to be very bright at times., The observation duration was noted to be between 20-25 minutes., The conclusion of the report was that the observed object was Venus., The witness, a 19-year-old female, has completed 12 years of elementary school and is a sophomore at Arkansas Tech., Two other individuals were present during the sighting.
witness description: female, 19 years old, social studies major at Arkansas Tech
